snippet.textDisplay: For anyone who believes as an axium that govt is incompetent, this video is a valuable lesson. While there are certainly people in govt like this lady who frankly don’t care at all about their constituents. There are also people like this gentleman who get into govt specifically because they care about their constituents. The problem becomes when people like her out number people like him and that happens when we the people turn a blind eye and just assume that everything will be ok. There are people in our govt, though I wish there were more, who will fight with every breath they have to do what is right for their people. But if we don’t support those people, if we allow the media to put them down for standing up to authority, if we hold our noses and continue to vote for the lesser of two evils and if we just plug our ears and shut our eyes because it’s too stressful, then when something we don’t see coming hits us, we shouldnt be surprised when there’s no one there to break our fall. Because we did nothing to make sure someone even COULD be there.

snippet.textDisplay: At first blush I can agree with most of the comments here.  However, after doing some research, it calls this into question as grand standing, for a few reasons.  First, at the time of this incident, he is running for a house seat. Second he knew the session was on camera. Third the issue with utilities was resolved before this meeting started. People's utilities were turned back on, any money was refunded for those that paid; he knew the situation was resolved.  (Keep in mind shutting off utilities already has a process in place.  In other words she never gave an order to shut utilities off, rather, an intervention was required to stop the process, which happened.) He was grandstanding on camera over an issue that he knew was resolved while running for a house seat.
